  <original-body>Before scopes, controller methods did this:

    @user = User.find(params[:id])

Now with scopes you can do

    @user = User.where(:id =&gt; params[:id]).first

However that doesn't raise an exception when the record is not found.  With this patch, you can do this:

    @user = User.where(:id =&gt; params[:id]).first!

And that raises the RecordNotFound exception, as you'd expect.</original-body>
